config RTL8196E_UART_BRIDGE
	bool "Realtek RTL8196E in-kernel UART<->TCP bridge"
	depends on MIPS && SERIAL_8250 && INET
	help
	  In-kernel byte shoveler between a TTY port (typically /dev/ttyS1,
	  the link to the Silabs EFR32 Zigbee/Thread radio) and a listening
	  TCP socket. Replaces the userspace serialgateway daemon so the hot
	  path can live in instruction SRAM (IRAM) and run without any user
	  context switch, which is required to sustain 460800 baud on the
	  Lexra RLX4181.

	  Protocol-agnostic: forwards raw bytes in both directions, used by
	  EZSP (NCP), CPC (RCP), and Spinel (OT-RCP) clients alike.

	  Must be built in (=y), not as a module. The IRAM gather in
	  vmlinux.lds.S only collects the .iram section from built-in code;
	  loadable modules keep their hot path in cached DRAM and defeat the
	  whole point of the driver.

	  If unsure, say N.
